<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,474,499]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[400,488,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) acutely produced posterodorsally; aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1050,1194,474,499]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
) with pair of short ventroapical processes, laterally divergent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="402" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,463,546,571]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Measurements (mm).</emphasis>
Male 
<typeStatus box="[554,657,546,571]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">holotype</typeStatus>
: body length 5.43; crown length 0.48; transocular width 1.33; interocular width 0.59; maximum pronotal width 1.38; forewing length 4.55.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,618,643]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Description.</emphasis>
Head (
<figureCitation box="[430,550,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) with median length of crown slightly more than 8/10 interocular width and slightly less than 4/10 transocular width. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[741,856,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) with width slightly greater than transocular width. Forewings with three closed anteapical cells; median cell longer than inner and outer ones. Hind legs with femoral setal formula 2:2:1; length of basal tarsomere similar to combined length of two succeeding tarsomeres.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
Male genitalia. Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[497,585,762,787]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, well produced posteriorly; posterior margin obliquely truncate with short dorsal projection; ventral margin with long, slender acute process turned posterodorsally, extending slightly beyond projection; dorsomedian portion of pygofer with group of long macrosetae; irregular longitudinal row of minute macrosetae on median portion of disc. Valve (
<figureCitation box="[981,1064,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) broad, subrectangular, posterior margin broadly convex. Subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[656,742,906,931]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) long, extending posteriorly slightly beyond pygofer apex; narrowed on apical half; apex rounded; ventral longitudinal row of long macrosetae; outer lateral and apical areas with long slender macrosetae densely arranged and some small macrosetae. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1131,1217,978,1003]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
) long and narrow, extending posteriorly much beyond connective apex; apical portion broad in lateral view; preapical lobe well produced; apex long and acute, curved outwards, with minute subapical tooth. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1186,1316,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
) Y-shaped in ventral view; arms moderately long; stalk short, with median keel. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1221,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
) long and narrow; dorsal apodeme conspicuous, slender; apical portion of shaft broadened; ventroapical margin produced, with pair of short divergent processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
Color. Dorsum (
<figureCitation box="[384,501,1194,1219]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) mostly brown with numerous pale yellow to ivory dots and small marks. Crown (
<figureCitation box="[159,272,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) brown mottled with pale yellow to ivory elliptical areas; two pairs of ivory elliptical spots, anterior one touching outer margin of ocelli, posterior one near posterior coronal margin. Ocelli red. Eyes brown. Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[159,272,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) pale brown mottled with pale yellow elliptical marks; pair of irregular small ivory maculae posterior to eyes. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[369,489,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 9, 10</figureCitation>
) mostly ivory with pair of irregular anterolateral brown areas. Forewings (
<figureCitation box="[1357,1428,1338,1363]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) translucent; veins mostly dotted with pale brown and white small areas; clavus with small ivory basal mark and two transcommissural ivory maculae bordered by brown, located on apex of claval veins; corium with basal veins of apical cells bordered by pale brown, apex fumose. Face with ground color yellow to brownish-yellow; frons dorsally continuing dotted pattern of crown; frontogenal sutures bordered by brown along a short area ventrally to antennal pits; upper portion of genae with yellow macula behind eyes; apical portion of labium pale brown. Thoracic sclerites mostly pale yellow laterally and ventrally. Legs pale yellow with brown areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,474,2011]" box="[199,400,1590,1615]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Female unknown.</paragraph>
