<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1770,1795]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[321,562,1771,1794]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="marica">
<emphasis box="[321,562,1771,1794]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Paraportanus marica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the male genital structures very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kramer, 1964" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1964" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eburatus">
<emphasis box="[1176,1436,1771,1795]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Paraportanus eburatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer" box="[158,322,1806,1831]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1964) A key for Portanus with new records and descriptions of new species (Homoptera: Cicadellidae: Xestocephalinae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 66, 5 - 11." type="journal article" year="1964">Kramer, 1964</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Kramer, 1961" authorityName="Kramer" authorityYear="1961" box="[345,648,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[345,462,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. elegans</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer" box="[479,640,1806,1831]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1961) New Venezuelan leafhoppers of the subfamilies Xestocephalinae and Neocoelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 74, 235 - 240." type="journal article" year="1961">Kramer, 1961</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Osborn, 1923" authorityName="Osborn" authorityYear="1923" box="[710,1057,1806,1831]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis box="[710,869,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. longicornis</emphasis>
(Osborn, 1923)
</taxonomicName>
. The pygofer of these species is posterodorsally produced and ventrally there is a long, acute slender process that is dorsally directed (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1430,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer" box="[151,305,1878,1903]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1964) A key for Portanus with new records and descriptions of new species (Homoptera: Cicadellidae: Xestocephalinae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 66, 5 - 11." type="journal article" year="1964">Kramer 1964</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 8; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer" box="[396,550,1878,1903]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1961) New Venezuelan leafhoppers of the subfamilies Xestocephalinae and Neocoelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 74, 235 - 240." type="journal article" year="1961">Kramer 1961</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 12; 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori" box="[654,848,1878,1903]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Linnavuori, R. E. (1959) Revision of the Neotropical Deltocephalinae and some related subfamilies. Annales Zoologici Societatis Zoologicae Botanicae Fennicae &quot; Vanamo &quot;, 20 (1), 1 - 370." type="journal article" year="1959">Linnavuori 1959</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 18 D). However, the new species has an acute projection dorsally (
<figureCitation box="[388,473,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) instead of a rounded short lobe. The aedeagi of 
<taxonomicName box="[1080,1211,1915,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eburatus">
<emphasis box="[1080,1211,1915,1939]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. eburatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1231,1349,1915,1939]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[1231,1349,1915,1939]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P. longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to that of the new species. They are long and broadened apically, with a pair of short processes ventrally (
<figureCitation box="[386,523,1986,2011]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer" box="[538,694,1986,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1964) A key for Portanus with new records and descriptions of new species (Homoptera: Cicadellidae: Xestocephalinae). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 66, 5 - 11." type="journal article" year="1964">Kramer 1964</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 7; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kramer" box="[789,945,1986,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Kramer, J. P. (1961) New Venezuelan leafhoppers of the subfamilies Xestocephalinae and Neocoelidiinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 74, 235 - 240." type="journal article" year="1961">Kramer 1961</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 9; 
<bibRefCitation author="Linnavuori" box="[1040,1235,1986,2011]" pageId="3" pageNumber="402" refString="Linnavuori, R. E. (1959) Revision of the Neotropical Deltocephalinae and some related subfamilies. Annales Zoologici Societatis Zoologicae Botanicae Fennicae &quot; Vanamo &quot;, 20 (1), 1 - 370." type="journal article" year="1959">Linnavuori 1959</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 18 B). In 
<emphasis box="[1415,1434,1987,2010]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="402">P.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">
<taxonomicName box="[151,236,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis box="[151,236,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[290,445,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis box="[290,445,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the processes are lamellar, while in 
<emphasis box="[848,951,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. m a r i c a</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1007,1133,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eburatus">
<emphasis box="[1007,1133,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. eburatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
they are slender. However, the new species has the aedeagal processes shorter and laterally divergent (
<figureCitation box="[991,1119,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 14" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1827,1850]" captionTargetBox="[198,1395,325,1739]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,303,1805]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 14. Paraportanus marica sp. nov. Male holotype: 9, dorsal habitus (antennae and legs not depicted; right forewing partially damaged); 10, head, pronotum, and mesonotum, dorsal view; 11, pygofer, lateral view; 12, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view (setae omitted in the left plate); 13, left style, connective, and aedeagus, dorsal view; 14, connective and aedeagus, lateral view. Abbreviations: C = connective, S = shaft of aedeagus. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258153/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">Figs 13, 14</figureCitation>
) when compared with those of 
<taxonomicName box="[181,307,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Paraportanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="403" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eburatus">
<emphasis box="[181,307,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="403">P. eburatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
